values:
So I have started subbing and I can already rule out that I do NOT want to teach pre-schoolers, middle schoolers, or special ed....just not my specialty.&nbsp; The subbing is fun though, it's awesome getting the opportunity to work with all different age groups and grades.&nbsp; It will really help me and give me the experience I will need when I start my certification come the spring.&nbsp; So far so good.

Wedding planning is coming along and it's so much fun.&nbsp; It's helping me to keep my mind off things while Tom is deployed.&nbsp; I have finally asked all my girls to be bridesmaids and we even found a dress for them!&nbsp; So exciting, especially because the dress is so super cute...I want one!!!&nbsp; My next order of business is DJ and photographer...both are going to expensive :/&nbsp; Oh well, we want our wedding to be amazing so it's worth it.&nbsp;&nbsp;

This time apart from Tom sucks.&nbsp; It never gets easy, no matter how many deployments one has been through...
I am focusing on planning an amazing future for us though, starting with an amazing wedding, then it'll be to get some things to furnish our beautiful duplex.&nbsp; Of course I am also focusing on improving myself.&nbsp; I am trying to be a more positive person and more responsible.&nbsp; It's so different knowing that in 8 months we are getting married and we are merging two lives together. It's not just dating, it's the biggest step that we both could ever take.&nbsp; We are very excited and know that we are both extremely blessed to have such a wonderful opportunity.&nbsp; I can't wait to call him my husband...no more fiance..I want to say I love my HUSBAND!&nbsp; Soon!!&nbsp; Also, I have been working out.&nbsp; I have trouble getting started so this time I got a personal trainer for 6 weeks.&nbsp; And let me tell you...it pays off!&nbsp; I have been working with her for not even a week and I have already improved on my endurance and lost 5 pounds!&nbsp; I eat pretty much what I want, as long as I watch my calorie entake and then workout.&nbsp; I do both cardio and weight training, both which are key factors if you want to have any kind of improvement.&nbsp; Doing just one or the other will not get the same results as doing both.&nbsp; I still have my trainer for 5 more weeks and I am anxious to see what happens!&nbsp;&nbsp;

I want to take a trip to C.S some weekend in the near future.&nbsp; I haven't been there since the beginning of August and I do miss my Aggies!&nbsp; Plus I want to hit up N.G :)&nbsp; It's been too long...
I need to look into taking a trip!!

Well, I guess that's about it for now.&nbsp; The biggest thing is that&nbsp;I am trying to stay positive&nbsp; and busy.&nbsp; I miss my baby so much but it's worth it because when he gets back we will be husband and wife!&nbsp;&nbsp;

Hope that everyone is doing well with school, work, life.
Talk to you all later~
